Seven persons have been arrested by police in Ondo for hijacking a truck conveying 900 bags of cement. The robbers also severely wounded the truck driver and left him for dead but heÂ  survived. Soldiers tracked the truck to Okitipupa where the robbers took it to. The police said the truck was moving from Ibese in Ogun State when the gang attacked it in the Ore axis of Ondo State. The suspects who were paraded at the Ondo police headquarters said they wanted to sell the cement for N4m. The mastermind of the robbery operation said he earned N35,000 in the firm where he worked as a truck driver. He said he wanted more money and had to inform other gang members. Ondo Police Commissioner, Bolaji, Salami, said the suspects would soon be charged to court.